SIMPLE: hydrometry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydrometry
<hw>Hy*drom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>hydrom⟦egrave⟧trique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of
determining the specific gravity of liquids, and thence the strength of
spirituous liquors, saline solutions, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art or operation of measuring the velocity or
discharge of running water, as in rivers, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydromica</ent>⟦br⟧
